{"award_age":61.0,"bio_image":"full\/038b9fe08ab9c3d1cdaf588d2566a4e9d02a163b.jpg","category":"Peace","country":"United States","date_of_birth":"1901-02-28T00:00:00.000Z","date_of_death":"1994-08-19T00:00:00.000Z","gender":"male","image_urls":["http:\/\/upload.wikimedia.org\/wikipedia\/commons\/thumb\/5\/58\/L_Pauling.jpg\/220px-L_Pauling.jpg"],"link":"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Linus_Pauling","mini_bio":"<p><b>Linus Carl Pauling<\/b> (February 28, 1901 \u2013 August 19, 1994)<sup id=\"cite_ref-frs_4-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Linus_Pauling#cite_note-frs-4\"><span>[<\/span>4<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup> was an American <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Chemist\" title=\"Chemist\">chemist<\/a>, <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Biochemist\" title=\"Biochemist\">biochemist<\/a>, <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Peace_activist\" title=\"Peace activist\" class=\"mw-redirect\">peace activist<\/a>, author, and educator. <i>New Scientist<\/i> reportedly called him one of the 20 greatest scientists of all time,<sup id=\"cite_ref-Horgan_5-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Linus_Pauling#cite_note-Horgan-5\"><span>[<\/span>5<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup> and as of 2000, he was rated the 16th most important scientist in history.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Sci100_6-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Linus_Pauling#cite_note-Sci100-6\"><span>[<\/span>6<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup> Pauling was one of the founders of the fields of <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Quantum_chemistry\" title=\"Quantum chemistry\">quantum chemistry<\/a> and <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Molecular_biology\" title=\"Molecular biology\">molecular biology<\/a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-natureobit_7-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Linus_Pauling#cite_note-natureobit-7\"><span>[<\/span>7<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup><\/p><p><span id=\"Nobels\"><\/span>For his scientific work, Pauling was awarded the <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Nobel_Prize_in_Chemistry\" title=\"Nobel Prize in Chemistry\">Nobel Prize in Chemistry<\/a> in 1954. In 1962, for his peace activism, he was awarded the <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Nobel_Peace_Prize\" title=\"Nobel Peace Prize\">Nobel Peace Prize<\/a>. This makes him the only person to be awarded two unshared Nobel Prizes. He is one of only four individuals to have won more than one Nobel Prize (the others being <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Marie_Curie\" title=\"Marie Curie\">Marie Curie<\/a>, <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/John_Bardeen\" title=\"John Bardeen\">John Bardeen<\/a>, and <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Frederick_Sanger\" title=\"Frederick Sanger\">Frederick Sanger<\/a>). Pauling is also one of only two people to be awarded Nobel Prizes in different fields, the other being <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Marie_Curie\" title=\"Marie Curie\">Marie Curie<\/a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Nobel_8-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Linus_Pauling#cite_note-Nobel-8\"><span>[<\/span>8<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup> Pauling also came close to being the discoverer of DNA's structure, another Nobel-worthy event.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Watson_9-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Linus_Pauling#cite_note-Watson-9\"><span>[<\/span>9<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup><\/p><p>In his later years he promoted <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Orthomolecular_medicine\" title=\"Orthomolecular medicine\">orthomolecular medicine<\/a>, <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Megavitamin_therapy\" title=\"Megavitamin therapy\">megavitamin therapy<\/a>, <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Dietary_supplements\" title=\"Dietary supplements\" class=\"mw-redirect\">dietary supplements<\/a>, and taking large doses of <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Vitamin_C\" title=\"Vitamin C\">vitamin\u00a0C<\/a>, none of which have gained acceptance in the mainstream scientific community.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Horgan_5-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Linus_Pauling#cite_note-Horgan-5\"><span>[<\/span>5<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Offit_10-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Linus_Pauling#cite_note-Offit-10\"><span>[<\/span>10<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup><\/p>","name":"Linus C. Pauling","place_of_birth":"Portland, Oregon","place_of_death":"Big Sur, California","text":"Linus C. Pauling , Peace, 1962","year":1962.0}